28/03/2005
NEW YORK, United States -- Greek Foreign Minister Minister Petros Molyviatis met with UN envoy Matthew Nimitz in New York on Sunday (27 March) to discuss how to accelerate the negotiation process in the name dispute between Macedonia and Greece.
Molyviatis reaffirmed his country's willingness to find a mutually acceptable solution to the problem.
In other news, Albanian President Alfred Moisiu visits Greece on Monday.
He'll be discussing bilateral issues with newly-elected Greek counterpart Karolos Papoulias.
(Kathimerini - 28/03/05;
ANA - 27/03/05;
Kathimerini - 26/03/05;
Albanian government Web site - 25/03/05)
